   "source": [
    "# Getting Started"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**This is not the finished tutorial. I am just testing the docker image**\n",
    "This notebook give a quick example of how scikit-gstat can be used to create meaningful variograms and utilize kriging classes to perform an interpolation."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "import numpy as np \n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from skgstat import Variogram, OrdinaryKriging\n",
    "plt.style.use('ggplot')\n",
    "os.environ['SKG_SUPPRESS'] = \"true\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The data is located in the `./data` subdirectory. We can load one of the examples and have a look at the data:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {

   ],
   "source": [
    "data = pd.read_csv('./data/sample_sr.csv')\n",
    "data.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},

    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [

    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(9, 9))\n",
    "art = ax.scatter(data.x,data.y, s=50, c=data.z, cmap='plasma')\n",
    "plt.colorbar(art)"

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Build a Variogram"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Warning: 'harmonize' is deprecated and will be removedwith the next release. You can add a 'SKG_SUPPRESS' environment variable to suppress this warning.\n",
      "Warning: compiled_model is deprecated and will be removed. Use Variogram.fitted_model instead. You can add an SKG_SUPPRESS environment variable to supress this warning.\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "e:\\dropbox\\python\\scikit-gstat\\skgstat\\Variogram.py:1668: UserWarning: Matplotlib is currently using module://ipykernel.pylab.backend_inline, which is a non-GUI backend, so cannot show the figure.\n",
      "  fig.show()\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x360 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "V = Variogram(data[['x', 'y']].values, data.z.values, normalize=False, maxlag=60, n_lags=15)\n",
    "fig = V.plot()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Kriging"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ok = OrdinaryKriging(V, min_points=5, max_points=15, mode='exact')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# build the target grid\n",
    "xx, yy = np.mgrid[0:99:100j, 0:99:100j]\n",
    "field = ok.transform(xx.flatten(), yy.flatten()).reshape(xx.shape)\n",
    "s2 = ok.sigma.reshape(xx.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.colorbar.Colorbar at 0x23ed58a2c48>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 7,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1152x576 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(16, 8))\n",
    "\n",
    "art = axes[0].matshow(field.T, origin='lower', cmap='plasma')\n",
    "axes[0].set_title('Interpolation')\n",
    "plt.colorbar(art, ax=axes[0])\n",
    "art = axes[1].matshow(s2.T, origin='lower', cmap='YlGn_r')\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('Kriging Error')\n",
    "plt.colorbar(art, ax=axes[1])"
   ]
  }
